deployedGeneratedSources.name: #utility.yul

devdoc.details: This implements an optional extension of {ERC721} defined in the EIP that adds enumerability of all the token ids in the contract as well as all token ids owned by each account.

_addTokenToOwnerEnumeration(Enumerable.E.details: internal function to add a token to this extension's ownership-tracking data structures.

params.to: address representing the new owner of the given token ID
params.tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be added to the tokens list of the given address

_removeTokenFromOwnerEnumeration(Enumera.details: internal function to remove a token from this extension's ownership-tracking data structures. Note that while the token is not assigned a new owner, the `_ownedTokensIndex` mapping is _not_ updated: this allows for gas optimizations e.g. when performing a transfer operation (avoiding double writes). This has O(1) time complexity, but alters the order of the _ownedTokens array.

params.from: address representing the previous owner of the given token ID
params.tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be removed from the tokens list of the given address
